And of course, whilst I work for myself,

00:30:23.920 --> 00:30:26.400
I love being able to set like the direction

00:30:26.400 --> 00:30:28.520
and strategy and everything.

00:30:28.520 --> 00:30:30.680
I'll be honest, pay pensions,

00:30:30.680 --> 00:30:34.359
being able to afford my own house, sweet, sweet benefits,

00:30:35.839 --> 00:30:40.839
cancelling my, in the UK, private medical insurance

00:30:40.839 --> 00:30:42.640
isn't a big deal.

00:30:42.760 --> 00:30:47.079
In the UK, private medical insurance isn't usually a thing,

00:30:47.079 --> 00:30:50.160
but we have fantastic private medical insurance

00:30:50.160 --> 00:30:53.599
with Microsoft that's helped cover my partner's transition

00:30:54.400 --> 00:30:58.359
entirely instead of it being like a 10 year

00:30:58.359 --> 00:31:02.400
agonizingly slow waitlist hell.

00:31:02.400 --> 00:31:05.000
Things like that have been so much better

00:31:05.000 --> 00:31:07.439
that I wouldn't have been able to achieve

00:31:08.680 --> 00:31:10.640
kind of running my own business

00:31:10.680 --> 00:31:13.199
than paying other people first.

00:31:13.199 --> 00:31:16.680
So big culture, pros and cons,

00:31:16.680 --> 00:31:21.040
and it's been a really useful enabler

00:31:21.040 --> 00:31:26.040
for kind of my circumstances to be more positive.

